FBIS3-48305 "dreas016_a_94010" FBIS-EAS-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Jan 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Ex-Im Bank Signs Loan Accord With PRC OW1801095294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0758 GMT 18 Jan 94 OW1801095294 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Tokyo, Jan. 18 Kyodo -- The Export-Import [Ex-Im] Bank of Japan said Tuesday [18 January] it signed an agreement to provide up to 40 billion yen in an untied two-step loan to the Bank of China to finance industrial projects. The government-funded bank said the money will be used for projects in Qingdao City, Shandong Province, and Hainan Province through the Chinese bank. The bank said the loan was first offered by the Japanese Government to China in August, 1988.
